WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.040
The following is a conversation with Kevin Spacey, a two-time Oscar-winning actor who

00:05.040 --> 00:11.360
has starred in seven The Usual Suspects, American Beauty, and House of Cards.

00:11.360 --> 00:17.140
He is one of the greatest actors ever, creating haunting performances of characters who often

00:17.140 --> 00:20.920
embody the dark side of human nature.

00:20.920 --> 00:25.960
Seven years ago, he was cut from House of Cards and canceled by Hollywood in the world when

00:25.960 --> 00:32.520
Anthony Rapp made an allegation that Kevin Spacey sexually abused him in 1986.

00:32.520 --> 00:38.920
Anthony Rapp then filed a civil lawsuit seeking $40 million.

00:38.920 --> 00:46.280
In this trial, and all civil and criminal trials that followed, Kevin was acquitted.

00:46.280 --> 00:52.280
He has never been found guilty nor liable in the court of law.

00:52.280 --> 00:57.920
In this conversation, Kevin makes clear what he did and what he didn't do.

00:57.920 --> 01:03.320
I also encourage you to listen to Kevin's Dan Wooten and Allison Pearson interviews

01:03.320 --> 01:09.360
for additional details and responses to the allegations.

01:09.360 --> 01:16.320
As an aside, let me say that one of the principles I operate under for this podcast and in life

01:16.440 --> 01:22.520
is that I will talk with everyone, with empathy and with backbone.

01:22.520 --> 01:28.040
For each guest, I hope to explore their life's work, life's story, and what and how they

01:28.040 --> 01:35.160
think, and do so honestly and fully, the good, the bad, and the ugly, the brilliance, and

01:35.160 --> 01:36.840
the flaws.

01:36.840 --> 01:43.160
I won't whitewash their sins, but I won't reduce them to a worse possible caricature

01:43.160 --> 01:45.200
of their sins either.

01:45.200 --> 01:50.480
The latter is what the mass hysteria of internet mobs too often does, often rushing to a final

01:50.480 --> 01:53.120
judgment before the facts are in.

01:53.120 --> 02:00.560
I will try to do better than that, to respect due process, in service of the truth.

02:00.560 --> 02:05.320
And I hope to have the courage to always think independently and to speak honestly, from

02:05.320 --> 02:10.360
the heart, even when the eyes of the outraged mob are on me.

02:11.000 --> 02:16.920
Again, my goal is to understand human beings, at their best and at their worst.

02:16.920 --> 02:23.280
And hope is such an understanding leads to more compassion and wisdom in the world.

02:23.280 --> 02:31.400
I will make mistakes, and when I do, I will work hard to improve.

02:31.400 --> 02:34.840
I love you all.

02:34.840 --> 02:36.480
This is the Lex Friedman podcast.

02:36.480 --> 02:40.080
